<paragraph id="8B8836B3BF3FFFDCFF60BD320829F922" blockId="3.[151,1436,1371,2008]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B943EAA1BF3FFFDCFF60BD320C02FAE6" box="[197,312,1371,1395]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Abdomen:</emphasis>
Dorsum with black pile on center of tergite one, except white hair on sides of tergite one, remainder with black pile; black tomentum with some white scales laterally on tergite six. Venter with black pile, not tomentose. Genitalia brown with black hairs; epandrium in lateral view, trapezoid, dorsal portion wider, cercus well exposed, epandrium subtriangular in dorsal view (
<figureCitation id="130C2A36BF3FFFDCFD73BDAE0E26FA4A" box="[726,796,1479,1503]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1967]" captionTargetBox="[325,1262,1172,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[325,1262,1172,1931]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Genitalia of male of W. plumipes. a, epandrium dorsal view; b, gonocoxite ventral view; c, epiphallus lateral view; d, epiphallus ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206541/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFF2494BF3FFFDCFCA8BDAE0E26FA4A" box="[781,796,1479,1503]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
a), posterior tip rounded, anterior corners elongated forward; gonocoxite in lateral view wider at middle with anterior hooked extension and posterior narrow tip; gonocoxite in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="130C2A36BF3FFFDCFE0CBE660CD5F9B2" box="[425,495,1551,1575]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1967]" captionTargetBox="[325,1262,1172,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[325,1262,1172,1931]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Genitalia of male of W. plumipes. a, epandrium dorsal view; b, gonocoxite ventral view; c, epiphallus lateral view; d, epiphallus ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206541/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFF2494BF3FFFDCFE44BE660CD5F9B2" box="[481,495,1551,1575]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
b) distinctly subquadrate, narrowing apically, anterior corners extending forward, medially divided; gonostylus with a basal process narrowing toward tip, tip slightly hooked in ventral view; epiphallus in lateral view slightly curved (
<figureCitation id="130C2A36BF3FFFDCFD26BE3E0FF1F9FA" box="[643,715,1623,1647]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1967]" captionTargetBox="[325,1262,1172,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[325,1262,1172,1931]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Genitalia of male of W. plumipes. a, epandrium dorsal view; b, gonocoxite ventral view; c, epiphallus lateral view; d, epiphallus ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206541/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFF2494BF3FFFDCFD1EBE3E0FF1F9FA" box="[699,715,1623,1647]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
c), apex swollen, hooked antero-dorsally; epiphallus in ventral view medially divided (
<figureCitation id="130C2A36BF3FFFDCFE02BE120CD7F906" box="[423,493,1659,1683]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1944,1967]" captionTargetBox="[325,1262,1172,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[325,1262,1172,1931]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Genitalia of male of W. plumipes. a, epandrium dorsal view; b, gonocoxite ventral view; c, epiphallus lateral view; d, epiphallus ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206541/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFF2494BF3FFFDCFE7BBE120CD7F906" box="[478,493,1659,1683]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
d), united only in apical third, basal half separated in two, wide at base narrowing toward apex, swollen near tip; aedeagus spine-like, slightly longer than epiphallus; gonopore terminal.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8836B3BF3FFFDBFF60BEAA095FFF41" blockId="3.[151,1436,1371,2008]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,825]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B943EAA1BF3FFFDCFF60BEAA0C77F94E" box="[197,333,1731,1755]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Pupal stage</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="130C2A36BF3FFFDCFEC5BEAA0C97F94E" box="[352,429,1731,1755]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1110,1133]" captionTargetBox="[294,1293,437,1085]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[294,1293,437,1085]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adult and pupa of male of W. plumipes. a and b dorsal and lateral view; c, wing; d, pupa, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/206540/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
Figs. 
<number id="3DFF2494BF3FFFDCFE06BEAA0C97F94E" box="[419,429,1731,1755]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
d): Integument of pupa yellowish hyaline with yellow setae and reddish brown blacktipped tubercles. Cephalic tubercles formed almost in straight line, medial tubercle situated slightly outside line between apices of anterior and posterior tubercles and closer to posterior tubercle. Tubercles broad basally, tapering to sharp apex, with sharp ventrolateral and dorsolateral ridges. Posterior tubercle short. Anterior facial tubercles compressed anteroposteriorly, connected by mesal ridge, with acute lateral apices. With a row of long curved bristles at the junction of the thorax and abdomen. Abdominal tergites two to six with a dorsal row of strong spines adhering to the cuticle except at their tips, tergite seven with a row of simple smaller spines, tergite eight without spines dorsally; sides of segments two to seven with a row of six wide, long flattened outgrowths, four in pleurites, two on sides of sternites. Anal tubercles about four times longer than medial width of one lobe, separated, broad basally, tapering to sharp apex, sclerotized at tip, slightly swollen dorsally before apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8836B3BF38FFDBFF60B8890F6CFF62" blockId="4.[151,1436,151,825]" box="[197,598,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="B943EAA1BF38FFDBFF60B8890C26FF6D" bold="true" box="[197,284,224,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="45">Female</emphasis>
. Not collected in this study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
